OL,6,FRepresenting him, Robert Thomas said:
OL,7,F"There is very little that can be said
OL,8,Fin Mr Brookfield's favour.
OL,10,F"He is extremely embarrassed, ashamed
OL,11,Fand very sorry about what he has done.
OL,13,F"Quite frankly, he is appalled by
OL,14,Fhimself."
OL,16,FMr Thomas said Brookfield had
OL,17,Fapologised in a pre-sentence report,
OL,18,Fas well as in letters to the court,
OL,19,Fand wanted to apologise again through
OL,20,Fhim.
