OL,6,FHe told the court Brookfield lives
OL,7,Fwith his partner, who is due to give
OL,8,Fbirth in February, and has caring
OL,9,Fresponsibilities for his teenage
OL,10,Fdaughter.
OL,12,FMr Thomas described the incident as a
OL,13,F"wake-up call" to his client, who had
OL,14,Fstopped drinking and taking drugs,
OL,15,Fadding that the prospect of prison
OL,16,F"terrified" him.
OL,18,FSentencing Brookfield, District Judge
OL,19,FMark Layton described how Mr Barton
OL,20,Fhad spoken about his cancer diagnosis.
